         ['Friction problems appear in FR as multi-part with FBD + calculation', 'Incline friction tested frequently in MC', 'Must distinguish static vs. kinetic friction based on context'],
         ['Find if a 10 kg block slides on 30¬į incline with őľ_s=0.6', 'A 5 kg block pulled at 15 N on őľ_k=0.3 surface; find acceleration'],
         [('A 10 kg block is on a 30¬į incline with őľ_s=0.6. Does it slide (g=10)?', ['mg sinőł=10(10)(0.5)=50 N (component down)', 'FN=mg cosőł=10(10)(‚ąö3/2)‚Čą86.6 N', 'Max static friction=0.6(86.6)‚Čą52 N', '52 N > 50 N ‚Üí block does not slide']),
          ('A 6 kg block is pulled with 30 N on a surface with őľ_k=0.25. Find acceleration (g=10).', ['FN=mg=6(10)=60 N', 'f_k=őľ_k¬∑FN=0.25(60)=15 N', 'F_net=30‚ąí15=15 N', 'a=15/6=2.5 m/s¬≤']),
          ('At what minimum angle does an object begin to slide if őľ_s=0.5?', ['Slides when tan őł > őľ_s', 'tan őł = 0.5 ‚Üí őł=arctan(0.5)‚Čą26.6¬į', 'Object slides for őł > 26.6¬į', 'Angle of friction depends only on őľ, not on mass']),
          ('A 4 kg block on a rough surface decelerates from 12 m/s to rest in 6 s. Find őľ_k.', ['a=(0‚ąí12)/6=‚ąí2 m/s¬≤', 'F_net=ma=4(‚ąí2)=‚ąí8 N (friction)', 'f_k=8 N; FN=mg=40 N', 'őľ_k=8/40=0.2']),
          ('Why is őľ_s > őľ_k in most cases?', ['Static friction must overcome molecular adhesion at rest', 'Once sliding starts, contact area and adhesion decrease', 'Kinetic friction involves less interlocking', 'Static friction requires more force to initiate motion than to maintain sliding'])],
