         ['Two blocks: 8 kg pulled by 40 N, connected to 2 kg on frictionless surface; find a and T', 'Atwood: m‚āĀ=6 kg, m‚āā=4 kg; find a and T'],
         [('Two blocks: 3 kg (A) and 5 kg (B), connected by string, pulled by 32 N on frictionless surface. Find a and T.', ['System: F=m_total¬∑a ‚Üí 32=8a ‚Üí a=4 m/s¬≤', 'Isolate A: T=m_A¬∑a=3(4)=12 N', 'Check B: 32‚ąíT=5(4) ‚Üí 32‚ąí12=20 ‚úď', 'T=12 N']),
          ('Atwood: m‚āĀ=8 kg, m‚āā=5 kg. Find acceleration and tension (g=10).', ['a=(8‚ąí5)¬∑10/(8+5)=30/13‚Čą2.31 m/s¬≤', 'T=m‚āĀ(g‚ąía)=8(10‚ąí2.31)=8(7.69)‚Čą61.5 N', 'Or: T=2m‚āĀm‚āāg/(m‚āĀ+m‚āā)=2(8)(5)(10)/13‚Čą61.5 N', 'Tension between weight and m‚āĀg: T < m‚āĀg']),
          ('A 10 kg block on a table is connected via rope over pulley to a hanging 4 kg block. őľ_k=0.2. Find a (g=10).', ['F_net=m_hang¬∑g‚ąíf_k=4(10)‚ąí0.2(10)(10)=40‚ąí20=20 N', 'a=F_net/(m‚āĀ+m‚āā)=20/14‚Čą1.43 m/s¬≤', 'Friction acts on table block only', 'T found by isolating hanging block']),
          ('In an Atwood machine, if both masses are equal, what is the acceleration?', ['a=(m‚āĀ‚ąím‚āā)g/(m‚āĀ+m‚āā)=0/2m=0', 'System is in equilibrium', 'Tension=mg (each mass)', 'Equal masses: no net force on system']),
          ('Why is tension the same on both sides of an ideal pulley?', ['Ideal pulley is massless and frictionless', 'No torque equation needed for massless system', 'Tension is an internal force transmitted through the rope', 'Real pulleys with mass would have different tensions on each side'])],
         [('https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yd1RgfCjLC8', 'Flipping Physics ‚ÄĒ Atwood Machine', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yd1RgfCjLC8')],
