      ('A 2 kg book rests on a shelf 3 m high. What is its gravitational PE relative to the floor? Relative to the ceiling at 5 m?', ['Relative to floor: PE=2(10)(3)=60 J', 'Relative to ceiling: h=3‚ąí5=‚ąí2 m; PE=2(10)(‚ąí2)=‚ąí40 J', 'Only differences in PE are meaningful', 'Reference choice is arbitrary']),
      ('A force of 100 N acts on a 10 kg object for 3 s. Find impulse and final speed if starting from rest.', ['J=FőĒt=100(3)=300 N¬∑s', 'őĒp=300 kg¬∑m/s; v_f=300/10=30 m/s', 'Impulse = change in momentum', 'v_f=30 m/s']),
